The paper involves using search engine queries and advertising systems to screen for cancer, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories. The use of clinically verified questionnaires and classifiers also involves machine learning and data analysis, which could fall under the social and information networks (cs.SI) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves medical applications and the use of technology to identify serious medical conditions, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
